<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?>
<bug>
    <id>316516</id>
    <title>Firefox fails to open a new window correctly while a print dialog is open in another window</title>
    <description>
        <paragraph id="2">
            <sentence id="2.1">If I open another Firefox window when an existing one has the print window open the new window doesn't appear correctly.</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.2">There are no tabs, no bookmarks, and the homepage doesn't load.</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.3">Additionally, I was testing while writing this and when the print window is open in the other session the text I type appears backwards!</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.4">!</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.5">siht ekiL</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="4">
            <sentence id="4.1">Steps to Reproduce:</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.2">1 Open a Firefox session</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.3">2 Open the print window</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.4">3 Open another session</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="5">
            <sentence id="5.1">Actual Results:  
The session opened at step three doesn't load any bookmarks, tabs or homepage.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="6">
            <sentence id="6.1">Expected Results:  
The session opened in step 3 should look like the one opened in step one</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="7">
            <sentence id="7.1">If the print window is closed then the behaviour returns to normal.</sentence>
            <sentence id="7.2">In order to test the backwards text open 2 browser windows, in one open the Print dialog box and then in the other type some text into a form.</sentence>
            <sentence id="7.3">Weird isn't it?</sentence>
        </paragraph>
    </description>
</bug>
